(443, 1, '2016-02-25 13:35:32', '2016-02-25 13:35:32', '<h1>Raffle Tickets Scholarship</h1>\r\n<h2>The 2016 raffleticket.com Scholarship Program is now open!</h2>\r\n<strong>“Impact a Life” College Scholarship 2016</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Your College Expenses Add Up Quickly – Let Us Help!</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Three Scholarships to be Awarded</strong>\r\n\r\nA – Z Printing, one of the nations leading producer of custom printed raffle tickets is offering a $1,000 – $600 and $400 “Impact a Life” Scholarship in order to help defray the expenses associated with the rising cost of college education.\r\n\r\nWe challenge the future leaders of America to provide creative solutions/ideas to serve their community, church, and service organizations through charitable acts of volunteerism.\r\n\r\nWe are pleased to award a Raffle Tickets Scholarship opportunity to motivated students to help in the furthering of their education. Our belief is that achieving a high grade point average should not be the only criteria for determining who needs to be helped.\r\n\r\nFor that reason we are offering a $1,000, $600, and $400 “Impact a Life” Raffle Tickets Scholarship Program that will be awarded for the three best essays we receive on one of the topics below. The recipients may use this money towards tuition or books.\r\n\r\n<strong>3 SCHOLARSHIP PRIZES to be AWARDED</strong>\r\n\r\n$1,000 – awarded directly to the winning recipient.\r\n$600 – awarded directly to the 2nd place winning recipient.\r\n$400 – awarded directly to the 3rd place winning recipient.\r\n\r\n<strong>HOW TO ENTER</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Write a 500 – 1000 word essay on one of the topics listed below.</li>\r\n	<li>Submit your essay, name, e-mail, phone number to:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="mailto:raffle-tickets-scholarship@raffleticket.com">raffle-tickets-scholarship@raffleticket.com</a> by 12/31/2016\r\n(Subject Line: Raffle Tickets Scholarship Essay)\r\n\r\n<em><strong>E-mail must contain your name, age, address, phone, and school you will attend in 2016. You may also include field of study, major declared, outside interests, etc.</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Essay must be submitted either in the body of the e-mail or as a Word attachment.</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<strong>ESSAY TOPICS</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><em>Describe how non-profit organizations, (including church groups, civic groups, youth sports organizations) can best derive benefit for their fundraising effort by holding a raffle fundraiser. Offer proposals for a) maximizing the sales of their raffle tickets b) prizes that would encourage and stimulate ticket sales c) suggested ways to motivate volunteers to sell more tickets.</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Describe how a business (including retail and service) can derive promotional and customer loyalty/retention benefit by utilizing a raffle in their marketing efforts.</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Chronicle a successful raffle fundraising campaign you or a family member has been a part of. What results were achieved? How did it help the organization and/or the community it was meant to benefit? How did the experience enrich you?</em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>WHO IS ELIGIBLE?</strong>\r\n\r\nOpen to students, 18 years and older enrolled in or accepted to an undergraduate, or graduate program at an accredited American university, college, or trade school within the 2016 calendar year. You must be a citizen of the U.S.\r\n\r\n<strong>ADDITIONAL TERMS &amp; RULES</strong>\r\n\r\nOWNERSHIP: By submitting an essay, you acknowledge and agree that: (a) Sponsor will own your application, including your written response submission, and (b) Sponsor will own all publishing rights in and to the written response essay submission. Suitable submissions may be posted on our blog, Facebook Page, Google Plus page, and other social media platforms.\r\n\r\nWinner must provide proof of enrolment in a U.S. university, college, or trade school before scholarship money will be awarded.\r\n\r\nSubmission deadline is December 31, 2016\r\n\r\n<strong>WINNING CRITERIA</strong>\r\n\r\nWinning essays will be awarded based on quality and relevance to the selected topic as well as social media participation. This includes the number of Facebook, Google Plus, Pinterest, and blog “likes,” followings, and comments.\r\n\r\nThe earlier your submission is received, the more opportunity you will have for social media interactions.\r\n\r\nAll other criteria used to determine the winner is solely at the discretion of A – Z Printing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Good Luck</strong>\r\n\r\n<iframe class="center-block"  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LSw9sE2AzQg" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>', 'Tickets Scholarship', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tickets-scholarship', '', '', '2016-02-25 13:35:53', '2016-02-25 13:35:53', '', 0, 'http://www.raffle.dev/?page_id=443', 0, 'page', '', 0);
